description:
&lt;p&gt;This new post will provide an exciting opportunity for a Physicians Associate to work in our busy oncology service based within the South West Wales Cancer Centre at Singleton Hospital in Swansea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Physicians Associate will support the trainee doctors in the delivery of high quality care to patients receiving non surgical oncology care and will be predominantly ward based.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must be interested in developing a sub specialty interest in oncology and will be expected to set up an oncology ambulatory care service based on service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Sarah GwynneJob titleConsultant Oncologist and Clinical Lead for OncologyEmail addresssarah.gwynne@eales.nhs.ukTelephone number01792 285828&lt;/p&gt;
